data.description: Welcome to this rustic mountain escape featuring a two-story sunroom with sweeping views of Heavenly ski slopes and the Tahoe National Forest.  Wood beams and paneling throughout provide a “cozy cabin” feel.  Vaulted ceilings and high windows make the living room/dining area spacious.  Upstairs bedrooms boast twin indoor balconies that overlook the sunroom and its expansive views. Truly a distinctive and relaxing home with oodles of storage, upstairs and down. This home is equipped with numerous “extras”, such as the heated driveway to lighten the snow burden, a wine cellar that doubles as a workout room, and an elevator that conveniently lifts up to four adults from the oversized two-car garage to the main level. This “envelope house” is heated by passive solar, as well as electric wall heaters that can be customized for each room, plus a large, efficient wood stove.  This (approximate) 2000 square foot classic Tahoe home has been well maintained and is move in ready.  The owners have made many upgrades to the kitchen, bathrooms and floors, and the wraparound decks have been recently stained.   The backyard provides privacy and overlooks US Forest Service land. The front yard is tastefully landscaped.
